We have two Timbers locations near us, the one off Stephanie and Horizon Rigde always seems to be a bit crowded, so this time we went to the one on Gibson and American Pacific in Henderson.
Nice!
we were the only ones for the dining room.
We had just received a $10 off coupon (for check over $20) and thought it was a great deal.
We both had the Timbers Western Bacon Cheeseburger and 2 soft drinks.
The burger was 1,000% awesome!
Huge meat patty that was actually square like Wendy's but a million times tastier!
I could have this Hamburger for a anniversay or birthday dinner!
I am not kidding its really that good!
With coupon the meal for 2 was $14 and change.
We left the waitress a good tip.
The service was great, the food was great and when we left the dining room started to fill up.
There was even some Policemen from Henderson PD there, so you know the food is good.
We've been having the Timber's Baby Bear Breakfast for years and other lunches and dinners.
We'll be back, coupon or not.
Whoever is cooking those burgers at night is doing a great job!
I want more!

