I'd never been to one of these but needed a drink after work one Saturday and BWW was entirely too crowded because of UFC.
Service at the bar was pretty good.
The drinks were reasonably priced.
But HOLY SMOKE.
I realize now why I NEED to go to a place like BWW's bar when I just want some drinks, because there's no smoking there.
But, naturally, since this place is 21 and over - unlike BWW - and has gaming you can smoke to your heart's delight.
And people do.
They nearly smoked me out of the place.
(I'm not judging, I just can't handle all that smoke sometimes.
And some places do a better job of "filtering" it than others).
I always get seemingly pretty good coupons for this place in the mail, the bar food looks pretty good, and I think they serve breakfast all day so it would be perfect for me here.
It is a good option for cheap drinks and gaming locally but the smoke will likely keep me away.

I stopped into this place on a Monday night with a co-worker during one of my business trips.
I found it to be a mixed bag, for me.
Keep in mind that I am not a sports bar person, so this review can be a little skewed.
The +'s:  The food portions were generous, and the items were generally tasty.
Pricing is reasonable, and service was good.
The -'s:  The place is not well lit (maybe a just my impression as lighting has a very real effect on TV viewing) and since it is a gaming/over 21 establishment, it was a little too smoky for my liking (something I should have known in advance-so my bad).
They do not accept American Express, so it did not work well for me or my business partner in that regard.
Overall, tasty food, attentive, friendly service.
Just not "my cup of tea" as they say.

